orwarded log records instead of only exercising a no-op API path.\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"agent_guidance\": \"Use a synchronous Log4j test path unless intentionally testing async loggers. Configure or build an OpenTelemetryAppender, install an OpenTelemetry SDK instance before logging, emit Log4j events, assert captured log records, and reset/stop Log4j/appender state between tests. No Docker image or required environment variable/system property is needed for the basic synchronous coverage path.\",\n      \"risks\": [\n        \"Async logger coverage is optional and would require extra setup such as Disruptor plus Log4j system properties set before Log4j initializes.\",\n        \"XML/plugin-based Log4j configuration may exercise additional native-image resource/reflection paths compared with programmatic builder setup.\"\n      ],\n      \"applied_setup\": [\n        {\n          \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n          \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.logging.log4j:log4j-core:2.17.2\",\n          \"result\": \"applied\",\n          \"target\": \"tests/src/io.opentelemetry.instrumentation/opentelemetry-log4j-appender-2.17/2.28.1-alpha/build.gradle\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n          \"coordinate\": \"io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-sdk-testing:1.62.0\",\n          \"result\": \"applied\",\n          \"target\": \"tests/src/io.opentelemetry.instrumentation/opentelemetry-log4j-appender-2.17/2.28.1-alpha/build.gradle\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"input_evidence\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"issue\",\n          \"summary\": \"#8544 Support for io.opentelemetry.instrumentation:opentelemetry-log4j-appender-2.17:2.28.1-alpha; label=library-new-request; body_chars=39\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"existing_tests\",\n          \"summary\": \"0 existing test file path(s) included\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\",\n      \"input_tokens_used\": 43987,\n      \"output_tokens_used\": 5253,\n